Haha okay, I get the frustration üòë ‚Äî this is 100% a CSS state issue, not Angular.

Below is a clean, complete sidebar CSS where:

‚ùå Nothing is highlighted by default

‚úÖ Highlight happens only on hover

‚úÖ Active state is applied only when you explicitly add a class

‚ùå No accidental background on load

‚ùå No :focus / :active surprises



---

‚úÖ sidebar.component.css (FULL & SAFE)

/* ========== SIDEBAR CONTAINER ========== */
.sidebar {
  width: 60px;
  height: 100vh;
  background-color: #1f2937; /* dark slate */
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  align-items: center;
  padding-top: 20px;
}

/* ========== SIDEBAR ITEMS ========== */
.sidebar-item {
  width: 100%;
  height: 55px;
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  cursor: pointer;
  color: #cbd5e1; /* light gray */
  transition: background-color 0.2s ease, color 0.2s ease;
}

/* ‚ùå NO DEFAULT HIGHLIGHT */
.sidebar-item {
  background-color: transparent;
}

/* ‚úÖ HOVER ONLY */
.sidebar-item:hover {
  background-color: #374151; /* gray hover */
  color: #ffffff;
}

/* ‚úÖ ACTIVE (ONLY if you add class manually) */
.sidebar-item.active {
  background-color: #2563eb; /* blue */
  color: #ffffff;
}

/* ========== ICON ========== */
.sidebar-item i {
  font-size: 18px;
}

/* ========== REMOVE UNWANTED STATES ========== */
.sidebar-item:focus,
.sidebar-item:active {
  outline: none;
  background-color: transparent;
}

/* ========== OPTIONAL TOOLTIP TEXT ========== */
.sidebar-label {
  display: none;
  position: absolute;
  left: 70px;
  background: #111827;
  color: white;
  padding: 6px 10px;
  border-radius: 4px;
  font-size: 12px;
  white-space: nowrap;
}

.sidebar-item:hover .sidebar-label {
  display: block;
}


